
- install arch - don't forget to install (and enable) networkmanager for internet after boot
- make user and update the sudoers file with visudo

- git clone https://github.com/sam-brysbaert/sams-dotfiles.git ~/.dotfiles

- git clone https://aur.archlinux.org/yay.git
- cd yay
- makepkg -si
- remove yay folder you just created

- cat ~/.dotfiles/setup-files/packs-to-install.txt | yay -S --needed -
- stow fish, misc, bspwm, etc.

- download secret files from drive
- run secret setup file

- in .dotfiles: git remote set-url origin git@github.com:sam-brysbaert/sams-dotfiles.git
- git clone git@bitbucket.org:yoymas/pass.git ~/.password-store

optional:
- install tlp and enable its service if on a laptop
- install nvidia drivers
